{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17641974","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17641974"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T19:34:32+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T19:34:32+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17920"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17920","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17920"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.09,0.78,0.09,0,0.03]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10634"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72827"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10634","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10634"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17920"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58297"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4943"},{"type":"tags","id":"5099"},{"type":"tags","id":"5102"},{"type":"tags","id":"10770"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24774"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24775"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72827","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/72827"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the mechanism of action of GLP-1 agonists?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Acts on the liver to reduce hepatic glucose production","Stimulates the secretion of insulin and inhibits release of glucagon","Activates AMPK to increase fatty acid oxidation","Inhibits mitochondrial complex I to reduce cellular energy balance","Reduces renal glucose re-absorption and causes glucosuria"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGLP-1 agonists\u003C/strong\u003E work by stimulating the secretion of insulin and inhibiting the release of glucagon, which helps in lowering blood glucose levels. They also slow gastric emptying and promote satiety, contributing to weight loss.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EReducing hepatic glucose production\u003C/strong\u003E is a mechanism associated with metformin, not GLP-1 agonists.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInhibiting mitochondrial complex I\u003C/strong\u003E is not a mechanism of GLP-1 agonists. This mechanism is more related to certain metabolic processes and drugs like metformin.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EReducing renal glucose re-absorption\u003C/strong\u003E and causing glucosuria is the mechanism of action of SGLT2 inhibitors, not GLP-1 agonists.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EActivating AMPK\u003C/strong\u003E to increase fatty acid oxidation is a mechanism associated with metformin, not GLP-1 agonists.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["GLP-1 agonists stimulate insulin secretion and inhibit glucagon release, which helps in lowering blood glucose levels.","GLP-1 agonists also slow gastric emptying and promote satiety, contributing to weight loss."],"references":["Bender, D. A., \u0026 Cunningham, S. M. (2021). Introduction to nutrition and metabolism. CRC Press","Salway, J. G. (2016). Metabolism at a Glance. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Banday MZ, Sameer AS, Nissar S. Pathophysiology of diabetes: An overview. Avicenna J Med. 2020 Oct 13;10(4):174-188. doi: 10.4103/ajm.ajm_53_20. PMID: 33437689; PMCID: PMC7791288","Galicia-Garcia U, Benito-Vicente A, Jebari S, Larrea-Sebal A, Siddiqi H, Uribe KB, Ostolaza H, Mart\u00edn C. Pathophysiology of Type 2 Diabetes Mellitus. Int J Mol Sci. 2020 Aug 30;21(17):6275. doi: 10.3390/ijms21176275. PMID: 32872570; PMCID: PMC7503727","Drucker DJ. GLP-1 physiology informs the pharmacotherapy of obesity. Mol Metab. 2022 Mar;57:101351. doi: 10.1016/j.molmet.2021.101351. Epub 2021 Oct 6. PMID: 34626851; PMCID: PMC8859548.","Sheehan MT. Current therapeutic options in type 2 diabetes mellitus: a practical approach. Clin Med Res. 2003 Jul;1(3):189-200. doi: 10.3121/cmr.1.3.189. PMID: 15931309; PMCID: PMC1069045","Aloke C, Egwu CO, Aja PM, Obasi NA, Chukwu J, Akumadu BO, Ogbu PN, Achilonu I. Current Advances in the Management of Diabetes Mellitus. Biomedicines. 2022 Sep 29;10(10):2436. doi: 10.3390/biomedicines10102436. PMID: 36289697; PMCID: PMC9599361"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58297"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17920"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58297","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/58297"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-22T08:51:18+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-22T08:51:19+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10634"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72827"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},